President Obama has nominated Justice Thomas Delahanty II and Wendy Olson to be United States Attorneys for the District of Maine and the District of Idaho, respectively. Justice Delahanty currently serves as a Justice for the Maine Superior Court, while Olson is currently Senior Litigation Counsel in the Office of the United States Attorney for the District of Idaho. President Obama expressed confidence that they will serve their respective districts with distinction and be resolute in their pursuit of justice.